President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation declaring February as National African American History Month. The proclamation recognizes the significant contributions made by African Americans to the United States and honors their resolve, resilience, and courage. The theme for this year's observance is "African Americans in Times of War," highlighting the heroic contributions of African Americans in the military throughout the nation's history. The proclamation also acknowledges the discrimination and challenges faced by African Americans, as well as their fight for equality and justice. President Trump calls upon public officials, educators, librarians, and all Americans to observe the month with appropriate programs, ceremonies, and activities.